From: Matthias Walther <m.walther@kluteq.de>
Subject: [PATCH] ath9k: force half-rate OFDM for ITS-G5 / DSRC band (5850-5925 MHz)

The 802.11p / ITS-G5 channels at 5850-5925 MHz are regulatorily defined
as 10 MHz wide. Userspace tooling that tunes the radio to those
frequencies (e.g. `iw dev mon0 set freq 5890 10MHz`) is supposed to
also pass the channel width down via cfg80211, but in practice the
width is often dropped on the way to the driver -- especially for
monitor-mode interfaces -- and chandef->width arrives as
NL80211_CHAN_WIDTH_20_NOHT.

Without CHANNEL_HALF set in ichan->channelFlags, the AR9580 PLL,
clock, and OFDM symbol timing in hw.c / ar9002_phy.c stay at 20 MHz
full-rate, the demodulator treats half-rate 11p frames as garbage, and
they get dropped as CRC errors before reaching netdev counters. The
previously-required workaround (echo 10 >
/sys/kernel/debug/ieee80211/phyN/ath9k/chanbw) only works because of
its side effect -- forcing a reconfig/reset -- and is fragile.

Fix this by treating the DSRC band as authoritative: if the tuned
center frequency lies inside 5850-5925 MHz, set CHANNEL_HALF
unconditionally and clear any HT/40 MHz flags that don't make sense
there. This makes update_ichannel produce a correct internal channel
descriptor regardless of what cfg80211 hands down, and removes the
need for any userspace debugfs poking.

Signed-off-by: Matthias Walther <m.walther@kluteq.de>
---
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath9k/common.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath9k/common.c
@@ -346,6 +346,19 @@
 		WARN_ON(1);
 	}
 
+	/*
+	 * ITS-G5 / DSRC: 5850-5925 MHz channels are regulatorily defined
+	 * as 10 MHz wide. cfg80211 / iw sometimes loses the width on the
+	 * way down (especially for monitor-mode interfaces) and we end up
+	 * here with chandef->width = NL80211_CHAN_WIDTH_20_NOHT. Force
+	 * half-rate based on the frequency alone so the PLL/PHY in hw.c
+	 * and ar9002_phy.c reprogram correctly without needing the chanbw
+	 * debugfs workaround.
+	 */
+	if (chan->band == NL80211_BAND_5GHZ &&
+	    chan->center_freq >= 5850 && chan->center_freq <= 5925)
+		flags = (flags & CHANNEL_5GHZ) | CHANNEL_HALF;
+
 	ichan->channelFlags = flags;
 }
 
